# Synapse Smart Contract Environment

## Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values:

```bash
# Private key for deployment (without 0x prefix)
PRIVATE_KEY=your_private_key_here

# 0G Testnet RPC URL
OG_RPC_URL=https://evmrpc-testnet.0g.ai

# 0G Storage Indexer URL (for metadata storage)
OG_INDEXER_URL=https://indexer-storage-testnet.0g.ai
```

## 0G Storage Configuration

For uploading agent reasoning traces to decentralized storage:

```bash
# Private key for 0G Storage transactions (generate new wallet, fund from faucet)
# This can be the same as PRIVATE_KEY or a separate key
OG_PRIVATE_KEY=your_private_key_here

# 0G Galileo Testnet RPC URL
OG_RPC_URL=https://evmrpc-testnet.0g.ai

# 0G Storage Indexer URL
OG_INDEXER_URL=https://indexer-storage-testnet-turbo.0g.ai

# 0G Flow Contract Address (FixedPriceFlow on testnet)
OG_FLOW_CONTRACT=0x22E03a6A89B950F1c82ec5e74F8eCa321a105296
```

### 0G Wallet Setup

1. **Generate wallet**: Use any Ethereum wallet generator or Hardhat
2. **Fund from faucet**: 
   - Visit https://faucet.0g.ai
   - Or request on Discord: https://discord.gg/0glabs
3. **Verify balance**: 
   ```bash
   npx hardhat console --network 0g-testnet
   > (await ethers.provider.getBalance("YOUR_ADDRESS")).toString()
   ```

## Contract Addresses (ADI Testnet - Chain ID 16602)

After deployment, contract addresses will be logged and saved to `deployments/0g-testnet.json`.

Copy these to your frontend environment variables (with NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix):

```bash
# Frontend Contract Addresses (0G Testnet - Chain ID 16602)
# These are exposed to the browser for contract interaction
NEXT_PUBLIC_COMPUTE_ROUTER=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_USDC=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_PROVIDER_REGISTRY=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_JOB_REGISTRY=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_ESCROW=0x...

# For local testing (Hardhat - Chain ID 31337)
NEXT_PUBLIC_COMPUTE_ROUTER_LOCAL=0x...
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_USDC_LOCAL=0x...
```

## Available Commands

```bash
# Compile contracts
npx hardhat compile

# Run tests
npx hardhat test

# Deploy to 0G Testnet
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.ts --network 0g-testnet

# Verify contracts (if supported)
npx hardhat verify --network 0g-testnet <CONTRACT_ADDRESS> <CONSTRUCTOR_ARGS>
```

